APPENDIX

A. ADDITIONAL HOMONYMS FORMED BY THE INFLECTION OF A SINGLE WORD

IN the Introduction, pp. xix-xxiv, instances are given where forms are duplicated in the course of the inflection of ordinary Latin words. These are all standard, classica] forms and are most of them in common use. All other instances of duplication of form within the inflection of a word, that are not thus outlined in the Introduction, have been entered in the Alpha- betical List, pp. 1-172. This is, of course, provided that they are found in actual use. These smaller groups of coinciding forms generally contain some earlier or more unusual word-form. The groups themselves may be conveniently shown in a tabular arrangement as follows: —
